    "contactZip": "98226",
    "description": "Many questions can be answered by reading through the text below. Kindly read the information before contacting us. Please note: The picture above is a stock photo.\nThank you for your interest in foster kittens! \nKittens who are in our foster care program are generally kittens who arrived at the humane society as unweaned orphans , were still nursing, or were not old or big enough to be placed up for adoption. These kittens would not have survived in a stressful shelter environment. Our foster care program provides care and comfort for animals with special needs in private homes of our trained volunteer foster care providers. \nOnce the kittens are old enough (usually 6-8 weeks) and weigh enough to be spayed or neutered (2 lbs), they return to the shelter for adoption. Call the shelter at (360) 733-2080 to inquire about available kittens. \nPlease note that we do not place âholdsâ on animals until youâve met them in person, even if youâve filled out an application and expressed interest in a specific animal. This is because we want to ensure that each animal is a good fit for the interested party, and that the interested party is a good fit for the animal. We try to set each adoption up for success, for both the animals and for the people.  \nThe kittens would love to meet you! Do you feel the same? Please fill out an adoption application (here or at either shelter) and turn it in to Emily Wyss the foster care coordinator via email at foster@whatcomhumane.org, or fax it to 360.733.4746. Our adoption counselors will help you figure out if you're right for each other.\n\nQuestions about foster kittens in general or other foster animals? Contact Alicia, Foster Care Coordinator, via  email at foster@whatcomhumane.org,or call 360.733.2080 x 3009. Many questions can be answered by reading through the above text. Kindly read the above information before contacting us. Thank you so much!\nPlease note that this is a stock photo.",
