    "description": "Every adoption requires an approved adoption application. Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete your application.\n\n Maggie is short hair female tabby with orange on her sides. She was born 3/15/15, weighs 2.12 lbs., is up-to-date on vaccinations but is not altered yet, is indoors only and fully litter box trained. Maggieâs siblings are Batman, Alistair, Madison and Boo. These little fur babies mamma was a drop off at a very nice persons home.  The owner took her in and loved her and cared for her and her kittens until they were old enough to be adopted.  Maggie is great with other cats, doesn't mind kids, and is totally comfortable with dogs. She is very calm, fairly laid back, and loves to be cuddled. But don't let her laid back personality fool you; she is super playful and loves all sorts of toys.  \n\nAn application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!",
