    "description": "Oliver is a sweet kitten who is shy to new people and situations. He will need a family dedicated to giving him the time and environment he needs to feel safe and comfortable to become a well-adjusted adult cat. He would do best in a home with adults only. It will be important to create a safe place where Oliver feels secure. We recommend providing a hidey-hole bed for your new feline. Feeding time and playtime will help create stronger bonds between you and your new family member. He will need toys and lots of time with you, but most of all she will need your patience and love to blossom to his full potential. If you feel you are ready to provide a lifetime of care and companionship to this little kitten, he will repay you with unconditional love. \n\nAll adoptions include: \nÂ· Spay/Neuter surgery \nÂ· FeLV tested \nÂ· FVRCPC vaccine and booster \nÂ· Microchip and free registration \nÂ· Free health check at a list of local veterinarians \nÂ· Free carrier and Cat Collar \n\nWe take in only stray and abandoned animals, so we may not have extensive knowledge of their behavior, but we'll do our best to make sure it is a good match.\n\nOur adoptions requirements are: \nÂ· You must be the registered home owner OR provide landlord approval \nÂ· All family members must visit your new kitty before finalizing the adoption. \nÂ· Any dogs in the home must have a current Rabies vaccine and license",
