    "description": "KONANI is a super cute and fluffy little female tabby kitten with white, orange, and brown highlights (often called a Torbie for tabby/tortie). She was found abandoned with her 3 sisters along the Willamette River, and was very underweight and had an eye injury. Her sister KALEA attempted to care for her by cleaning her and cuddling with her. Konani has blossomed into a super sweet, happy, and playful kitty with some medical care and with the loving attention of her sister. She is a lover; she will play and then she likes to get some human snuggling. Her cute little black nose checks out everything (you can tell her apart from Kalea who has an orange nose). Because Konani and Kalea are so bonded, we are asking that they be adopted together, and are offering them at a reduced price of $150 for the pair (instead of $110 per kitten), sponsored by the McIntosh family. She has been tested for feline leukemia and FIV (she is negative), spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, defleaed and dewormedâplus you get a free vet visit. Konani and Kalea are temporarily in foster care. For more info, call Beth at (541) 255-9296",
