    "adoptable": true,
    "contactEmail": "annioakly@aol.com",
    "contactZip": "97405",
    "description": "Hello ladies and gentlemen,\nAllow me to introduce myself. \nI am a Siamese one year old female. My name is Zuri. It means beautiful in Africa. Which you can see, fits me perfectly. My foster mother says I am the most beautiful feline she has ever seen! I am soft, super sweet and loving too. With a playful side. I have a long coat which sheds a bit so hair balls might become an issue when I groom myself, but so far it hasn't. \nI like to sit with my human and enjoy gentle loves and pets. Naps of course is my favorite activity most of the day. I am not too finicky about my food and I don't bite, scratch, or fight which means that any other animals or humans in the home have to be respectful of me other wise they might hurt me when I don't fight back. \nI absolutly love sitting in a window and watching the birds and squirrels. I love it so much that I chatter at them and want to run outside any chance I get and chase them! I am so fast and silent that my foster mom gets scared when she can't find me. A little kitty trick I play on her every once in awhile, haha. My foster mom won't let me outside because she says it is the rescues rules and I might get lost or hit by a car outside, or since I am so beautiful, someone might catnap me. She takes really good care of me to ensure I am safe and happy! I love wet food, but it is starting to make my trim waist line get a little plump, so I can only have it for a treat or a tiny bit each day. My foster mom leaves fresh dry food and water out for me all day. I love a nice warm and soft place to sleep. The back of the couch or her bed is great, but the dogs chase me. \nI like to play too! I have this one toy which my foster mom bought for me and it's so cool! It only cost $1 at the pet store and entertains me for quite awhile. Sometimes I lose it which can be frustrating for me but my foster mom always finds it and she said she will let me take it with me to my new family home!! \nWell that is alot of information about me so I really hope the right family finds me and adopts me forever! My foster mom sure does love me but she wants me to be in a permanent home of my own for the rest of my life which will be a long time since I am only one years old. I would love to meet my family soon. Wouldn't that be a superb Christmas gift for me?!\nThank you for reading my long bio. I just wanted you to know everything about me so you can make the best decission for your family and me!\n\nSincerely,\nZuri the beautiful\n\nPlease contact us for more details 541-782-THOR (8467) or fill out our application on our website under adoption application at www.theheartofrescue.com.",
