    "description": "ADOPTED! Our appreciation to all who wanted to provide this dog with a loving home. Unless otherwise requested, any adoption applications we received will be kept on file for future adoption consideration.\n\n* Female Domestic Long Hair/ Maine Coon\n* Approximately 5 months/years old\n* Approximately 4 lbs.\n* Litterbox trained\n* Okay with other cats\n* Okay with dogs\n* Adoption fee: $100\n\nRaising a kitten requires a lot of work and is a commitment! Jorie will be an awesome addition to a family that can give her the attention, exercise, training and affection she deserves.\n\nHealth: Jorie has been spayed and microchipped. She is current on her vaccines and tested negative for Feline leukemia virus (FeLV) and feline immunodeficiency virus (FIV). She has been wormed and flea treated.\n\nHistory: Jorie comes from another local rescue. PUP was asked to help and we are so glad we did. \n\nNotes from Jorie's Foster Home:\n\nLittle Jorie is the sweetest and the most feminine little kitty I've met.She is fairly reserved as in a little shy if her surroundings become too busy; she prefers to observe from the sidelines, if at all.  She is not into racing and chasing....it's as though she regards it as \"unladylike\".   Jorie does love her cat tree; climbing high to watch the birds, napping or an occasional tango with a hanging toy.\n\nIn the evenings, when the fur kids are quietly hanging out, watching TV or sleeping, Jorie comes along and joins pups and kitties alike, in my lap so she can gather up her fair share of love!!!  She is VERY affectionate.  She will climb on you like a cat tree....back of the chair behind your head, on your head, your shoulders...all while purring quite loudly, to the tune of some dance routine only she can see or hear.\n\nDuring the day when she's not sleeping on the basket of laundry, I'm most apt to find her sleeping upstairs on my bed.  Jorie's favorite friend is my older cat, Tomas.  Tomas is my 15 lb. retired farm cat and mouser who is also not interested in the teenage play of \"catch me if you can\", racing up and down the stairs.  I often see him lazing about on the bed washing Jorie's face.\n\nJorie is one who would shine her brightest as an only kitten with an adult kitty friend or maybe a teenage friend that is also happier living the mellower life, much like herself.  I believe Jorie would love playing as long as her mate was not as rambunctious as her current housemates!  She would also feel very blessed if her new home included a nice, high kitty tree.  :) \n\n{ Note: The above description reflects the behavior we have observed in the cat's foster home. Although PUP provides adopters up to the minute information on our cats, we cannot guarantee they will behave in the same manner in a different environment with new owners. } \n\nAdoption: If you think you have room in your home and heart for this dog and you reside within Washington State, please go to our Adoption Information page. There you will find more information and be able to fill out an adoption application.  http://www.pupdogrescue.org/adopt.html",
