    "description": "**Important Note** You won't find this kitty at the shelter. This kitty is waiting patiently in foster care for your call. Please contact the Foster Care Hotline at 206-684-0685 to arrange a meeting. Thank you! Rob Roy is a sweet young, energetic boy who loves to run and play. If you throw a treasured toy across the room he will gladly chase after it and then entertain you with some one-cat soccer. He loves to climb and explore or dart across the tile floor and slide under the sofa to retrieve a lost toy. Have dust bunnies in hard to reach places? Rob Roy will gladly find them for you and pull them out into the open! Favorite toys include the laser, shadows, and a small soft ball filled with catnip. Though timid at first and hesitant to be pet, Rob Roy enjoys human companionship and especially likes to follow you around the house and observe all you do. He is particularly attuned to meal times , eager to remind you when it's time to be fed. Rob Roy is not a clingy cat but once he feels comfortable, will happily snuggle at your feet as you're waking up in the morning! Rob Roy adores other cats and would find himself quite lonely without a patient older brother or sister to play with and continue his studies in all things feline. He would do best in a somewhat quite home with both people and cats willing to play with him. Older kids, or patient younger children, should be OK. Rob Roy has been treated for a gastrointestinal condition in the past and needs a guardian who can commit to always feeding him a particular grain-free diet to keep him healthy. This food is easily found at local pet stores or vet offices [or possibly on line where it might be cheaper?]. In return for this minimal care, he will make a handsome, healthy, and entertaining companion.",
