    "contactZip": "98021",
    "description": "Micah and Kelby are cute, sweet, and fun.  These two sisters are almost identical, and they absolutely love attention.  They are always exploring, playing, cuddling, and practically purr just thinking someone might come into the room.  Their mother was seen jumping out of a trailer that was being moved from one junk yard to another.  At the new location, two tiny kittens were found hiding under the trash.  These girls were instantly happy with whatever life had given them despite the sad beginnings.  Now they are looking and waiting for a great home to appreciate all the love they have to give!  Micah and Kelby are not Cat Tales cats but are being posted as a courtesy for another rescuer. \nIf you would like to meet Micah and Kelby please email fortheloveofcush@gmail.com.\nUpdate from their foster mom, straight from the girls' mouths....\n\nHi! How are you doing?! We know it's not really the right forum in which to ask, but we're just such polite girls that we couldn't resist, and we absolutely love making new friends! You should also probably know that we'v  been told that we're the best kind of friends to have because we can make anyone smile (no matter what kind of day they've had) with our infectiously happy and enthusiastic personalities and affinities for snuggles.  We can liven up even the most boring tasks with our always interested presence and selfless offers of assistance, and we pretty much radiate sunshine with our gentle but loud purrs, prances with tails raised, and soft head bonks. So, if you're looking for two new best friends who were born with the ability to make every one of your days better just by being ourselves, our foster family is pretty sure the slogan \"who rescued who?\" was written with us in mind!  Please email fortheloveofcush@gmail.com to find out more about us!\n\nP.S. We're about 7-months-old, spayed, vaccinated, FIV/FeLV tested, microchipped, and litterbox trained!",
