    "description": "Jimmie is a sweet little boy. He is a young kitten, who was born to a very loving stray mom cat. Oasis got a call from a nice couple who found a litter of kittens under a tarp that was covering the cushion on their deck swing! Oasis went over and gathered up the kittens and also found their mom, Angel, who is also available for adoption. Jimmie and his litter mates were about 5 weeks old and were all brought inside, where Angel raised them. Jimmie is one of 5 kittens and really loves his litter mates. Jimmie would do best if adopted into the same home with one of his litter mates to play with. Kittens do best if they have a buddy to play with. Jimmie gets along well with everyone, but will be shy of new surroundings at first. He requires a family that will give him lots of attention and time to adjust. When adopting a kitten, the human family needs to understand that kittens are active and get into mischief, plus they do require lots of time, attention and patience. It's also necessary to understand that kittens will need the time to adjust to the new situation. Jimmie is a cute boy, with glossy black fur, with a touch of white and big round eyes. Adopting an animal is a lifetime commitment, so please do not adopt until you can make that commitment. Jimmie is neutered, vaccinated, flea treated and wormed. If you are interested in adopting him, please fill out and submit our on-line application, which is on our website at www.oasisforanimals.org or let us know if you have any questions. We are located on the south end of Whidbey Island, about 15 minutes from the ferry landing in Clinton. We normally take cats to various locations on the mainland on the weekends for adoption, so please just ask or check our Facebook page. Thank you for adopting a homeless, rescued kitty!",
