    "contactEmail": "katies.place@shaw.ca",
    "contactZip": "V2W 1A4",
    "description": "** TALK TO US ABOUT A POSSIBLE PERMANENT FOSTER SITUATION FOR BEANS**\n\nSweet Baby Beans was born with Manx Syndrome (a form of Spina Bifida) where essentially his spine is too short for his body. Baby Beans doesnât careâ¦ he frolics and plays like any other kitten. However, his case is extreme and he is also bowel and bladder incontinent.\n\nThis incontinence caused his people to bring him to be euthanized. The vet just could not euthanize a roly, poly, playful, purring baby (we are so very fortunate to work with so many kind, compassionate vets) so they asked us if we could help. Incontinent animals are a challenge from a practical perspective, and Beans will also need to be closely monitored as he will be susceptible to infections.\n\nWe donât know how long he will be with us, but he is here now. He is joyful and he is greatly loved.",
