    "description": "Ainsley is always ready for an adventure or a game! Hide and seek? Yes! Chase the feather? Yes! Roll and tumble with her siblings? Of course! If she's not busy playing, she's snuggling up with her foster folks and taking a nap. Sweet, silly, and loving, Ainsley would probably do best with another kitten to play with, as well as a nice human lap to cuddle in. Ainsley was born in the wrong place--in the backyard of someone who hates cats! The property owner wanted them gone right now and drove her mom away. Luckily the property owner let us remove the kittens before they came to harm, so Ainsley and her kitten buddies, Grier and Ramsey, went to an experienced bottle feeder who took great care of them. Now she is a bright-eyed, friendly, loving and playful kitten ready for a home of her own. If you would like to meet Ainsley, please go to our Karma Rescue APPLICATION page. Please be as thorough as possible when completing it. Thank you! November 18, 2015, 8:33 pm",
