    "description": "DOB: 4/1/15 Unagi was the first of his litter to be trapped and fixed, which is why he has an eartip. He came to us underweight and with a bad cold, from living in an industrial use lot in South Gate. Once we realized how tiny and friendly he was, we knew he had to be fostered. Unagi is spunky, loving and likes to feel that he is in charge. He is an affectionate cat and will snuggle in bed and on the couch. Gets along wonderfully with older cats who are amenable to kittens. Do not recommend as a solo cat. His whole litter (nicknamed the Sushi Kittens) are bonded and adopting a pair of them would make for excellent lifetime companionship for these guys. Unagi rolls over for belly rubs, just like all his siblings. His chirping meow and high flying leaps during feather toy playtime will steal your heart. Playful, active but also gentle and VERY sweet. Walks with the cutest little bow legged strut! We adore him. Siblings names are: Nori, Tako, Tamago, Miso, Toro. If you are interested in learning more about this kitty or in adopting him, please click here to email his foster parent or 617-794-2382.If you are unable to send an email to the foster parent through the link included above, please contact us and let us know what kitty you're interested in. You may also fill out our adoption questionnaire to speed up the screening process. Be sure to specify the cat you're interested in at the end of the questionnaire!For our fees and adoption policies and procedures, please click here. November 20, 2015, 12:43 pm",
